# Enterprise Supplemental Terms (Non‑Conflicting)

These supplemental terms enhance enterprise clarity while remaining fully compliant with the permissive nature of the MIT License. They do **not** introduce additional restrictions but provide guidance for professional, commercial, and enterprise environments.

## 1. Commercial Use

The Software is approved for unrestricted commercial deployment, including integration into proprietary products, managed services, SaaS offerings, and enterprise environments.

No additional licensing fees or royalties are required. Organizations may operationalize, automate, or embed the Software in internal or customer-facing platforms.

## 2. Attribution (Recommended for Enterprise Compliance)

Attribution is not legally required but is strongly encouraged in professional and enterprise environments to maintain transparency and provenance.

Recommended format:
**"Powered by IAC Dharma — [https://github.com/Raghavendra198902](https://github.com/Raghavendra198902)"**

Attribution may be placed in:

* product documentation,
* about/configuration screens,
* compliance or OSS notice bundles,
* internal architecture documentation.

